The paper discusses security and authentication protocols for Device-to-Device (D2D) communication in mobile networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves the development of analytic models and implementation on mobile devices, which could fall under information theory (cs.IT), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), and software engineering (cs.SE).
